name: iShares S&P U.S. Financials Index ETF
longDescription: The ETF will primarily invest in U.S. equity securities and/or securities of one or more ETFs managed by BlackRock or an affiliate. The ETF currently seeks to replicate the performance of the S&P Financial Select Sector Index (the Index). The Index is comprised of equity securities of issuers in the S&P 500 Index that are categorized into the GICS sector of Financials (40). Financial companies in the Index can include companies involved in activities such as banking, mortgage finance, consumer finance, specialized finance, investment banking and brokerage, asset management and custody, corporate lending, insurance and financial investment and transaction and payment processing services. The ETF seeks to provide longterm capital growth.
